# Dependabot PR Processing Gate

When Dependabot (or similar) PRs are open, **do not leave them idle**. Process each PR specifically and comprehensively.

## Per-PR checklist

1. Read the PR title/diff (package, from→to, files).
2. Classify: patch/minor (prefer adopt) vs major (compat review + tests).
3. Rebase/reconcile with current `main` (or active feature base).
4. Run quality gates impacted by the change (`typecheck`, `lint`, `test:run` / `test:coverage`, `build` as needed).
5. Fix breakages in the same change set (types, eslint config, lockfile, workflows).
6. Prefer a **tested consolidation PR** when many Dependabot PRs overlap/conflict; then comment on each original PR with disposition (merged into #N / superseded / deferred with reason).
7. Trigger/address CodeRabbit on the resulting PR before merge (see `011-coderabbit-pr-gate.mdc`).

## Do not

- Bulk-close Dependabot PRs without testing or a written disposition.
- Merge majors (e.g. lucide-react 0→1, vitest 3→4) without gates green.
- Leave Actions bumps only on `deploy.yml` while `security.yml` stays stale.

English for PR comments/docs (`010-english-content.mdc`).

<example>
Open Dependabot PRs for `actions/checkout` and `dompurify` → land both in one consolidation branch, run `typecheck`/`lint`/`test:coverage`/`build`/`audit`, document disposition in `docs/dependabot-disposition.md`, comment each Dependabot PR with link to the consolidation PR, close superseded PRs, leave majors deferred with reason.
</example>

<example type="invalid">
Close all open Dependabot PRs in bulk without running gates or writing per-PR disposition comments.
</example>
